description:
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a competent and enthusiastic individual to join our community paediatrics team in the role of medical secretary for safeguarding.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a new role created to support the management of the safeguarding service across Cwm Taf Morgannwg UHB.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be a key point of contact for safeguarding queries and referrals, and will be responsible for typing letters, managing the patient pathway and supporting the doctors that take part in the safeguarding rota.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post will form a key part of the secretarial team and will take the lead for aspects of administrative work within the department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate will have secretarial and typing experience, will have worked in an NHS setting previously, and will have a positive and flexible approach to work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: 8th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Amanda Morgan&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Administration Manager Community Paediatrics&lt;/p&gt;
